I"Ê<p>We are proud and honoured to have been awarded the <a href="http://geospatialworld.net/News/View.aspx?id=33263_Article&amp;utm_content=buffer3ad98&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_source=twitter.com&amp;utm_campaign=buffer">Geospatial World Leadership Award for Research Institution of the Year 2015</a>.</p>

<p>The award, which we share with other research groups at the TU Delft in the field (such as <a href="http://www.gdmc.nl">GIS-technology</a> and the <a href="http://www.citg.tudelft.nl/over-faculteit/afdelingen/geoscience-and-remote-sensing/">Geoscience &amp; Remote Sensing</a>), recognises our crucial role in geomatics and our contributions to the fields of 3D geoinformation, among others.</p>

<p>The award will be presented during the <a href="http://geospatialworldforum.org">Geospatial World Forum</a> in a few month in Rotterdam.</p>

